    "explanation": "PR 471 changed control-plane admission (environment_manager.py, environments.py, cli.py) and bumped the Environment Manager lock generation from 1.3.0 to 1.4.0 (a new additive EnvironmentLock field), and the worker build-provenance generator now emits the canonical source_commit key; all of these change the v8 wheel content hash and the sealed environment lineage. NONE of them changes the worker execution closure (the worker/supervisor/artifacts/runners/trainer runtime bytes that execute optimizer steps); the only closure-adjacent change is an additive optional contract field that defaults to null with no runtime behavior change. A fresh v8 wheel and environment pair is therefore required because the wheel artifact identity and manager lock generation changed, not because worker execution changed - unlike the v6->v7 transition, which was a genuine worker-execution change (the training_step token observer in training/trainer.py).",
